text: Typhoon Phanfone, known in the Philippines as Typhoon Ursula, was a strong tropical cyclone to hit the central of the Philippines, on December 25, 2019.https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/12/19/19/brewing-christmas-storm-creeps- closer-to-philippines-pagasa https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/12/25/19/mga- apektado-ng-ursula-malungkot-ang-pasko On December 24, 2019 at 16:45 in the Philippines, typhoon Ursula was located at the vicinity of Boracay island, in the town of Malay, Aklan into a Category 3 "typhoon". Typhoon Phanfone struck the central and southern part of Luzon on Christmas day, 2019. It left at 57 dead particular in Iloilo province and more than 6 are missing.https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/12/18/18/lpa-to-dampen-mindanao-a-week- ahead-of-christmas ==Typhoon Storm Warning Signal== PSWS LUZON VISAYAS MINDANAO PSWS #3 Masbate, Occidental Mindoro, Oriental Mindoro, Coron, Palawan, Romblon Aklan, Antique, Biliran, Capiz, Bantayan, Cebu, Iloilo, Leyte, Eastern Samar NONE PSWS #2 Albay, Burias, Masbate, Marinduque, Sorsogon Samar, Northern Samar NONE PSWS #1 Batangas, Camarines Norte, Camarines Sur, Cavite, Laguna, Metro Manila, Quezon, Rizal Bacolod, Cebu, Southern Leyte Dinagat, Surigao del Norte ==References== Category:2019 disasters in Asia Category:2019 Pacific typhoon season Category:Tropical cyclones in Asia Category:Retired tropical cyclone names Category:Aklan
